Hilton in KwaZulu-Natal is on high alert. This as South Africa's first case of coronavirus is believed to be from the area. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Hilton in KwaZulu-Natal is on high alert. This as South Africa's first case of coronavirus (COVID-19) is believed to be from the area. Cowan House Preparatory School has responded by closing its doors. READ: South Africans living in China afraid to return home Teams are on the ground tracing those who had contact with the infected 38-year-old man. The man's wife and kids are not showing any symptoms yet and are taking necessary precautions. The patient and his wife were part of a group of 10 people who arrived back in South Africa from Italy on 1 March.